
They're the kind of photos Anthony Maloney would rather not have. One shows soggy books in his home office. Another shows him in a respirator mask peeling moldy insulation from his walls. A third shows his living room stripped down to the studs. "We've lost everything," he said. Despite his status as a flood victim, he's gotten no Red Cross debit card, no lump-sum FEMA check, little rental assistance and even less attention from government bureaucrats. 

